Installation:

    git clone git://github.com/dmayle/dm-dotfiles.git ~/.dm-dotfiles

Create symlinks:

    ln -s .dm-dotfiles/vim ~/.vim
    ln -s .dm-dotfiles/bash/bashrc ~/.bashrc
    ln -s .vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc

Switch to the `~/.dm-dotfiles` directory, and fetch submodules:

    cd ~/.dm-dotfiles
    git submodule update --init

Switch to the '~/.vim/bundles/pyflakes' directory, and fetch submodules (This
is necessary because the pyflakes.vim submodule uses a submodule of its own for
the pyflakes python module; The sed is necessary because it assumes write access to the repo):

    cd ~/.dm-dotfiles/vim/bundles/pyflakes
    sed -i 's":"/"; s"git@"https://"; s"\.git""' .gitmodules
    git submodule update --init

Add this to your crontab to auto-update everyday at 3am.
    0 3 * * * echo $(cd ~/.dm-dotfiles && git pull https://github.com/dmayle/dm-dotfiles) >/dev/null

Software required:
    Mac:
        MacVim (in order to get a vim compiled with python and ruby support)
        Exuberant Ctags (the BSD ctags that comes with OSX is bad)
